The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | LIC puts up good show 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       LIC puts up good show 
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                          R.R Dash in Calcutta on Tuesday. A Telegraph picture                                  
	Calcutta, June 24: State-owned Life Insurance Corporation of India earned an income of Rs 40,655 crore from investments in 2007-08.         
	R.R. Dash, LIC zonal manager (east), said, The insurer gained Rs 10,000 crore from the sale of equities alone in 2007-08.         
	During the last financial year, the LIC made an investment of Rs 1,50,303 crore and at the end of March this year, the companys mark-to-market value of investments stood at Rs 7,51,000 crore, up from Rs 6,70,000 crore in 2006-07, Dash said.        
	Out of its Rs 1,50,303-crore investment in the last financial year, the LIC pumped Rs 11,633 crore into infrastructure projects such as roads, bridges and power.         
	Our cumulative investment in the infrastructure sector as on March 31, 2008 stood at Rs 56,691 crore, Dash said, adding that this was in addition to the LICs investments in social infrastructure projects such as water management and housing.         
	In 2007-08, the LIC invested Rs 5,635 crore in social sector projects, and the cumulative investment figure at the end of the financial year stood at Rs 32,321 crore, Dash said.                                                                                                                                                               
